text: SmugMug is a platform that helps
photographers run their businesses.

We manage and run all of
their back office software
for them, allowing them
to spend their time focused on actually
helping their customers.

The challenge we were trying
to address was getting business
insights out of our application data
so we could make better business decisions

with our customers on
which products to offer
and at which price points.

Working with AWS, we were able
to increase the efficiency

of the data team working
with unfamiliar code bases
to glean the insights that they needed
to complete the data model

for the reporting
requirements that we had.

We were using Amazon Q
Developer to take the
data model from the application

and mix it with
application data to be able

to ultimately generate
a Redshift data table

that we could then do business
analytic reporting on.
From there, Q was able

to help us then build an
actual machine learning model

that we could use for predictive
analytics of what to expect
for each of our individual customers.

Q Developer has really increased
developer productivity in

some cases by as much
as a hundred percent.

The ability for developers
to work in unfamiliar code,
to not have to get out

of flow state have been
really transformative

for their ability to execute
and deliver projects on time.

Building on AWS's technology
platform has really allowed
us to take opportunities that we wouldn't
otherwise be able to take advantage of.

As a technology provider
that we trust with all
of our customer data,
it's a real accelerant for us.
